{
  "texts": [
    "According to the authors, all routers in the CCNCheck verify the content's signature with the same probability.",
    "When the probability of signature verification is high (more signatures are checked at a time), this increases the processing overhead of the router.",
    "Furthermore, in a CCNCheck the same packet is verified repeatedly, which can create latency and overhead.",
    "To cover the above-mentioned shortcomings, the authors propose a content pollution mitigation mechanism that consists of two different deployment approaches which are discussed below.",
    "• Deployment Approach 1 (DA 1): In this approach, the in-network routers are classified into two different sets; (border routers and core routers)."
  ]
}